How to install
Example path on Windows:

Place in lua directory 

 
/lua run party
/lua stop party  to stop

Use /party to open the UI, set your five warp points, then zone to another area.

You’ll see a new file appear in E3/MQ2/lua/party/ named after the new zone (e.g., shardslanding.lua). When you return to the original zone, its warps are loaded again automatically.

Now each zone has its own persistent warp set stored in a nicely‑named file. Enjoy! 🚀
